  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rwanda Social Protection Programme Additional Financing</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Currently finalising negotiations, expect to be approved by Bank Board at end of March or early April at which time a PAD will be available. The PON funding is being processed as &#x2018;additional financing&#x2019;, essentially a top up, to the IDA project. It happened in this way because the timing for the cash transfer project was late relative to the broader social protection.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Decrease the percentage of children under 5 years with height-for-age z-score below -2 standard deviations from a baseline of 43.6% to 32% Decrease percentage of children under 2 years with height-for-age z-score below -2 standard deviations from a baseline of 37.1% to 27.2% Increase percentage of children 6-23 months old who are fed a diverse diet from baseline of 22.9% to 50% Increase percentage of women who attended 4 or more ANC visits during their most recent pregnancy from a baseline of 41% to 55%</narrative>
  </description>
